Subject: Derived Task Frame Routing Worker Latch Source

Description: Preserved derived source for the task-frame routing worker latch observed during task_frame_routing_012 LM Studio worker benchmarking.

& [DerivedTaskFrameRoutingWorkerLatchSource] is preserved derived source
  + [source_type] is derived_from_benchmark_observation
  + [observed_subject] is corpus_task_frame_routing_012
  + [initial_failure] is worker produced correct routing fields and required terms but emitted non-ASCII mojibake in authority_boundary
  + [accepted_retry] is retry 001 passed after the prompt used a copy-exact eight-line ASCII SOP output with explicit authority_boundary and evidence_gate fields
  + [derived_latches] is authority_boundary_latch, ascii_stability_check, and copy_exact_output_latch
  + [reason_for_change] is authority-sensitive routing tasks need ASCII-stable boundary wording before worker output can become readiness evidence
  + [outside] is hidden model state, broad LM Studio competence, project-root authority, and worker mutation authority

  = must: preserve the failed attempt as benchmark data
  = must: treat retry success as one family signal only
  = must: keep Codex as validator and integration authority
  - never: treat correct routing fields as accepted when authority boundary text is encoding-damaged
